    console.log(\`Running ESLint analysis on \${projectPath}...\`);\r
    const absolutePath = path.resolve(projectPath); // Ensure the path is absolute\r
\r
    // Change directory to the project path and run npm run lint\r
    execSync(\`cd \${absolutePath} && npm run lint\`, {\r
      stdio: "inherit",\r
      shell: true,\r
    });\r
\r
    console.log("ESLint analysis completed and report generated.");\r
  } catch (error) {\r
    // Check if the error is due to a non-zero exit code from ESLint\r

      console.warn("ESLint found issues, but the analysis completed.");\r

      // Counting number of lines of code in project\r
      await getLinesOfCode(projectPath);\r
      // Optionally, you can log the error message or any other details if needed\r
    } else {\r
      console.error("Error running analysis: ", error.message);\r
    }\r
  }\r
};\r
\r
module.exports = analyze;\r

const fs = require("fs");\r
const path = require("path");\r
const { createSpinner } = require("./spinner");\r
\r
const getLinesOfCode = (projectPath) => {\r
  console.log("Counting line of codes... on path:", projectPath);\r
  const spinner = createSpinner();\r
  try {\r
    const excludeListPath = path.join(__dirname, "../exclude-list.txt");\r
\r
    const result = execSync(\r
      \`npx cloc \${projectPath} --exclude-dir=node_modules --exclude-list-file=\${excludeListPath} --json\`\r
    );\r
    fs.writeFileSync(\r
      path.join(__dirname, "../reports/line-of-code.json"),\r
      result\r
    );\r

    stop: () => {\r
      clearInterval(spinnerInterval);\r

  };\r
